  "notes": "Standard Sindhi (Pakistan/India). Typologically remarkable: four implosives /ɓ ɗ ʄ ɠ/ — rare in Indo-Aryan. Full four-way laryngeal contrast plus implosives. Written in Perso-Arabic (Pakistan), Devanagari (India), and the Khudabadi script (traditional).",
